# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js project with a well-organized structure. Here are the key directories and their purposes:

## Core Directories

- `app/`: Contains the main application routes and layouts using Next.js 13+ App Router
  - `(website)/`: Public website routes
  - `(auth)/`: Authentication-related routes
  - `(admin)/`: Admin panel routes
  - `forex/`: Forex trading related routes
  - `restricted/`: Protected routes
  - `api/`: API route handlers
  - `actions/`: Server actions for data mutations

- `components/`: Reusable React components
  - `ui/`: Basic UI components
  - `trading/`: Trading-related components
  - `room/`: Room management components
  - `voice-room/`: Voice chat components
  - `profile/`: User profile components
  - `navigation/`: Navigation components
  - `livekit/`: LiveKit integration components
  - `admin/`: Admin panel components

- `lib/`: Utility libraries and shared code
- `utils/`: Helper functions and utilities
- `hooks/`: Custom React hooks
- `types/`: TypeScript type definitions
- `providers/`: React context providers
- `public/`: Static assets
- `data/`: Data-related files and configurations

## Key Files

- `middleware.ts`: Next.js middleware for route protection
- `next.config.ts`: Next.js configuration
- `tsconfig.json`: TypeScript configuration
- `package.json`: Project dependencies and scripts
- `components.json`: Component configuration
- `postcss.config.mjs`: PostCSS configuration
- `eslint.config.mjs`: ESLint configuration

## Documentation

The project includes several markdown files documenting different features:
- `task.md`: Task management documentation
- `ranking.md`: Ranking system documentation
- `record.md`: Record keeping documentation
- `follower.md`: Follower system documentation
- `admin.md`: Admin panel documentation
- `funds.md`: Funds management documentation

